title: CreativeLIVE - Taking Care of Business with Tamara Lackey
description:
CreativeLive - Taking Care Of Business With Tamara Lackey
English | 2 Day | Audio: aac, 44100 Hz, stereo, s16, 125 kb/s | Video: h264, yuv420p, 852x480, 817 kb/s, 28.00 fps | 3.06 GB
Genre: Video Training


Tamara Lackey is a professional photographer with a passion for creating authentic lifestyle photography, from children's portraits to commercial and editorial projects, her work is praised within her industry and published internationally.

Tamara's work has been featured in dozens of media outlets including Vogue, O - The Oprah Magazine, Town & Country, Parenting Magazine, Food & Wine, The Knot, Professional Photographer Magazine, Rangefinder Magazine, Shutterbug Magazine, NBC's "The Martha Stewart Show" and ABC's "Extreme Makeover: Home Edition". Her educational book for professionals, "The Art of Children's Portrait Photography," was released in late 2008, quickly followed by her next projects - an instructional video titled "Inside Contemporary Children's Photography," in partnership with Rex Ballard, and the "Tamara Lackey Style Guide," with Kubota Image Tools. In 2010 Tamara and Rex Ballard released their next project, "Tamara Lackey's Capturing Life Through (Better) Photography", an instructional DVD, book, on-the-go reference guide, and gift set to consumer audiences
